    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0838}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.} The entry is represented by the operator carrier\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}.\n\\]\n\nInsert the carrier into the ordered TRAWIN chain as\\[\nC_{0838}=N\\circ I\\circ W\\circ A\\circ R\\circ T(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}).\n\\]\n\nThe derivation closes when the chain returns the normalized operator:\\[\nC_{0838}=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}},\\qquad \\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\nThus the Nonary derivation for [ID 0838] is the three-stage passage\n\\[\n\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0838}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}},\n\\]\nwith the entry title fixing the meaning of the carrier and the TRAWIN normalization fixing the admissibility test.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.} TZPID ENTRY 0838 is therefore an operator-level Nonary step: the named process is not accepted as a loose label until it survives TRAWIN ordering and closure.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
